cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on Device-to-Device (D2D) communications in mobile data networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper proposes admission and power control methods for D2D communications to increase network capacity while maintaining QoS. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possibility as the paper considers different levels of complexity and available channel state information (CSI) in a multi-cell environment. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as proximity-based applications mentioned in the abstract may involve multimedia content. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may discuss security issues related to D2D communications.
